io.nats.client

Interface SyncSubscription

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AutoCloseable, Subscription

    public interface SyncSubscription
extends Subscription
    A client uses an SyncSubscription object to receive messages from a subject synchronously.

    • Method Detail

      • nextMessage

        Message nextMessage()
             throws IOException,
                    InterruptedException
        Receives the next Message that becomes available for this Subscription, waiting if necessary until a Message becomes available.
        Returns:
        the next message produced for this subscription, or null if the Connection is closed concurrently.
        Throws:
        InterruptedException - if interrupted while waiting, e.g. because the Subscription was closed in another thread
        IOException - if the Subscription has been unsubscribed due to reaching its autoUnsubscribe limit, or if the Subscription has been marked a slow consumer.
        IllegalStateException - if the Subscription is not valid, e.g. it was closed prior to this invocation
        See Also:
        Subscription.autoUnsubscribe(int)

      • nextMessage

        Message nextMessage(long timeout)
             throws IOException,
                    InterruptedException
        Receives the next Message that arrives for this Subscription, waiting up to the specified wait time if necessary for a Message to become available.
        Parameters:
        timeout - how long to wait before giving up, in milliseconds
        Returns:
        the next message produced for this subscription, or null if timeout expires before a message is available
        Throws:
        InterruptedException - if interrupted while waiting, e.g. because the Subscription was closed in another thread
        IOException - if the Subscription has been unsubscribed due to reaching its autoUnsubscribe limit, or if the Subscription has been marked a slow consumer.
        IllegalStateException - if the Subscription is not valid, e.g. it was closed prior to this invocation
        See Also:
        nextMessage(long, TimeUnit), Subscription.autoUnsubscribe(int)

      • nextMessage

        Message nextMessage(long timeout,
                    TimeUnit unit)
             throws IOException,
                    InterruptedException
        Receives the next Message that arrives for this Subscription, waiting up to the specified wait time if necessary for a Message to become available.
        Parameters:
        timeout - how long to wait before giving up, in units of unit
        unit - a TimeUnit determining how to interpret the timeout parameter
        Returns:
        the next message produced for this subscription, or null if timeout expires before a message is available
        Throws:
        InterruptedException - if interrupted while waiting, e.g. because the Subscription was closed in another thread
        IOException - if the Subscription has been unsubscribed due to reaching its autoUnsubscribe limit, or if the Subscription has been marked a slow consumer.
        IllegalStateException - if the Subscription is not valid, e.g. it was closed prior to this invocation
        See Also:
        Subscription.autoUnsubscribe(int)
